<div class="section--padding{% if section.settings.show_divider %} section--divider{% endif %}">
  <div class="page-width{% if section.settings.narrow %} page-width--inner{% endif %}">
    <div class="faq">
      <div class="title-wrapper-faq{% if section.settings.heading == blank %} title-wrapper--no-heading{% endif %} {{ section.settings.heading_alignment }} home-faq-title">
        <{{ section.settings.heading_tag }} class="title {% if section.settings.home %} faq-title{% endif %} {{ section.settings.heading_size }}">
          {{- section.settings.heading | escape -}}
        </{{ section.settings.heading_tag }}>
      </div>

      <div class="home-faq collapsible-faq">
        <accordion-tab class="accordion" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
          <details
            {% if section.settings.open_first_collapsible_row and forloop.index0 == 0 %}
              open="open"
            {% endif %}
          >
            <!-- First Row -->
            <summary>
              <span class="summary__title">
                <p class="accordion__title h3">Product & Ingredients</p>
              </span>
              <span class="icon icon-plus-alt"></span>
            </summary>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">Do you use high-quality ingredients?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                All our ingredients are fully biodegradable. Seacra products are formulated with the highest quality,
                natural, organic, biodynamic and wild-harvested ingredients that have been ethically sourced by
                companies who care about your health and the health of our planet.

                If you have questions about any of the ingredients do not hesitate to email us at contact@seacra.com
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">Are your products cruelty-free?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>Yes! We never test our products on animals and never will.</p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">Are Seacra products suitable for all skin types?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                All Seacra products are suitable for dry, oily, combination and sensitive skin. However, due to the high
                lipid component of red algae, hydration is at its core, meaning Seacra products are especially effective
                at replenishing and healing dry, irritable, and sensitive skin.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">Where are Seacra products made?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>All our products are developed and manufactured in Spain.</p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">Who are Seacra products suitable for?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Our products have been clinically tested and are safe for all ages and skin types including pregnant
                women.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">How can one product be suitable for everyone?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Red algae activate a cascade of natural processes within your skin encouraging it to heal and recover by
                itself. Red algae also amplify the work of any other natural ingredient in your skin regimen.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">
              Can I replace other products in my skin regimen with Seacra?
            </button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                We encourage people to cleanse, tone, Seacra, SPF and go however, those with particularly dry or
                sensitive skin may still need to moisturise. Astaxanthin (the bioactive compound in red algae) is 6,000
                times more potent than Vitamin C and 100 times more potent than vitamin E in combatting reactive
                oxidative stress. It is also ten-times richer in vitamin A (a natural alternative to retinol), a super
                hydrator with a greater moisturising effect when compared to hyaluronic acid and increased
                anti-inflammatory activity when compared to most anti-inflammatory drugs.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion__content rte typeset">
              <!--
                {{ block.settings.row_content }}
                {{ block.settings.page.page }}
              -->
            </div>
          </details>
        </accordion-tab>
        <accordion-tab class="accordion" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
          <details
            {% if section.settings.open_first_collapsible_row and forloop.index0 == 0 %}
              open="open"
            {% endif %}
          >
            <!-- Second Row -->
            <summary>
              <span class="summary__title">
                <p class="accordion__title h3">The science behind Red Algae</p>
              </span>
              <span class="icon icon-plus-alt"></span>
            </summary>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">What makes your Red Algae gel different?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Our innovative cold-processing technique allows us to preserve the highest concentrates of vitamins and
                minerals as well as nutrients in our products. Without using heat extraction, we cold press our
                ingredients, which makes our Red Algae gel ten times more potent than any others on the market.

                If you have questions about any of the ingredients do not hesitate to email us at contact@seacra.com
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">What are the unique properties of Red Algae?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Red Algae offers the ultimate multipurpose skincare product for all skin types. The active ingredient,
                Astaxanthin, has the following skincare properties: anti-aging (14%), antioxidant (39%),
                anti-inflammatory (14%), anti-melanogenic (7%), anticancer (5%), and antimicrobial (21%).
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">How will Red Algae help reduce my skin pigmentation?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Red Algae helps reduce your skin pigmentation in two ways. Firstly, it inhibits the overproduction of
                melanin synthesis (the most common reason for skin pigmentation). Secondly, it contains one of the most
                powerful antioxidants, Astaxanthin, which has been proven to be 6,000 times more potent than Vitamin C
                and 100 times more potent than Vitamin E in combating free radicals. It is these free radicals that are
                responsible for activating the overproduction of melanin and causing pigmentations and dark patches.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">How can Red Algae help with Eczema flare-ups?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                People with eczema have an impaired skin barrier, which can cause dryness and other issues. Red algae's
                polysaccharides have a greater moisturizing effect when compared to hyaluronic acid, and contain
                powerful antioxidants that shield your skin from many environmental stressors that can cause flare-ups.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">
              How can the benefits of Red Algae be helpful to Rosacea sufferers?
            </button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                People with Rosacea have higher levels of abnormally processed cathelicidins, which are inflammatory
                mediators that are part of the skin's defense system. The polysaccharides in Red Algae appear to have
                greater anti-inflammatory activity than most anti-inflammatory drugs and may help reduce inflammation
                caused by rosacea.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="collapsible">Do I need to use SPF if Red Algae protects from UV rays?</button>
            <div class="content">
              <p>
                Yes, while Red Algae has many potent antioxidants, it is always important to wear sunscreen. Cleanse,
                tone, Seacra and then SPF. To prevent premature ageing, the antioxidants in red algae combined with the
                SPF in your sunscreen are known as the perfect combination for healthy, youthful skin.
              </p>
            </div>
